						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅgachōḻa. Year 8: A.D. 1157.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Records that Cheviḍai Periyāṉ, Naḍuviṟ Periyāṉ and Chiṟup Periyāṉ, the three potters <hi rend="italic">(vēṭkōvaṉ)</hi> who held the right of supplying earthern ware pots to the temple of Muttūr in Kāṅgaiya-nāḍu received one and half <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> from the authorities of the temple of Kulōttuṅgachōḻīśvaram Uḍaiyār and probably agreed to supply earthern ware vessels to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
